WEBVTT

00:01:57.823 --> 00:02:00.704
She has experienced so many tears of life,

00:02:00.728 --> 00:02:05.029
and is therefore the perfect person
to talk about how to be color-brave

00:02:05.053 --> 00:02:07.347
in every arena of society.

00:02:07.863 --> 00:02:10.592
Mellody, you're joining me
from San Francisco,

00:02:10.616 --> 00:02:12.744
I'm so happy to get to talk with you.

00:02:12.768 --> 00:02:15.815
MH: Thank you so much for having me,
I'm delighted to be here.

00:02:15.839 --> 00:02:18.958
CA: So I'd love to start with
a little more about your background.

00:02:18.982 --> 00:02:22.172
Can you give us
a picture of you as a child,

00:02:22.196 --> 00:02:24.572
like, what it was like growing up?

00:02:24.596 --> 00:02:26.668
MH: Well, I grew up
the youngest of six kids

00:02:26.692 --> 00:02:28.824
and I'm really young in my family.

00:02:28.848 --> 00:02:31.985
My oldest sister is more
than two decades older than me,